-- Africa Industries Gains Most Since October After Agreement
-- B y   S h o s h a n n a   S o l o m o n
-- 2012-05-29T13:57:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-29/africa-industries-advances-most-in-a-month-on-distribution-deal.html
Africa Israel Industries Ltd. (AFID)  rose
the most in more than seven months after the maker and importer
of steel coils and ceramic tiles said a unit signed a
distribution agreement with a Canadian company.  The  shares  advanced 3.5 percent, the most since Oct. 18, to
252.50 shekels at the 4:30 p.m. close in  Tel Aviv .  The company signed a 400 million-shekel ($103 million)
distribution pact with Olympia Tile International Inc., a
construction material manufacturer.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Shoshanna Solomon in Tel Aviv at 
 ssolomon22@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Maedler at 
 cmaedler@bloomberg.net  